    "Computational screening of putative targets can be performed via several bioinformatic tools (see for example refs.",
    "4, 5), made available on the Immune Epitope Data Base (IEDB) 6 and other web servers [7] [8] [9].",
    "The methods primarily gaining momentum and prominence among these tools are the ones from Machine Learning (ML), the ensemble of algorithms and model architectures to learn from data in such a way as to better analyze them and make new predictions (see Box 1 for the basic ML terminology).",
    "Several ML-based reverse vaccinology pipelines have been developed [7] [8] [9] [10] [11] [12] [13] [14] [15], with promising applications to the prediction of bacterial protective antigens 7, [10] [11] [12] and Sars-Cov-2 antigens 8, [13] [14] [15].",
    "ML can assist several stages of vaccine design 16, but its application is particularly key to a fast and accurate target selection during the initial phase (Fig. 1a)."
